(10, 'test@gmail.com', 'Straight Hair', 'Normal', 'Frizzy hair', 'Oily', 'Dandruff', '2-3 days', 'Yes,Heavy dandruff', 'None', 'Other Hormonal Issues', 'Disturbed sleep,I wake up atleast once a night', 'High', 'Never', 'both', 'No', 'Very low in the afthernoon', 'None', ''),
(11, 'test@gmail.com', 'Straight Hair', 'Normal', 'Frizzy hair', 'Oily', 'Dandruff', '2-3 days', 'Yes,Heavy dandruff', 'None', 'Other Hormonal Issues', 'Disturbed sleep,I wake up atleast once a night', 'High', 'Never', 'both', 'No', 'Very low in the afthernoon', 'None', ''),
(12, 'test@gmail.com', 'Straight Hair', 'Normal', 'Frizzy hair', 'Oily', 'Dandruff', '2-3 days', 'Yes,Heavy dandruff', 'None', 'Other Hormonal Issues', 'Disturbed sleep,I wake up atleast once a night', 'High', 'Never', 'both', 'No', 'Very low in the afternoon', 'None', 'Okay, based on your answers, it seems you\'re dealing with several hair and scalp concerns: frizzy straight hair, oily scalp, heavy dandruff, and potential hormonal imbalances affecting your hair.  Let\'s address these individually:\n\n**1. Frizzy Straig'),
(13, 'test@gmail.com', 'Straight Hair', 'Normal', 'Frizzy hair', 'Oily', 'Dandruff', '2-3 days', 'Yes,Heavy dandruff', 'None', 'Other Hormonal Issues', 'Disturbed sleep,I wake up atleast once a night', 'High', 'Never', 'both', 'No', 'Very low in the afternoon', 'None', 'Okay, based on your answers, it seems you\'re dealing with several hair and scalp concerns: frizzy straight hair, oily scalp, heavy dandruff, and potential hormonal imbalances impacting your hair. Let\'s address these individually:\n\n\n**1. Frizzy Straight Hair:**\n\n* **Hydration is key:**  Since your hair is straight and prone to frizz, it likely lacks moisture. Use a moisturizing shampoo and conditioner designed for straight or fine hair. Look for ingredients like hyaluronic acid, glycerin, or shea butter.\n* **Leave-in conditioner:** Apply a lightweight leave-in conditioner or a smoothing serum to help tame frizz and add shine.\n* **Avoid sulfates and silicones:**  Sulfates can strip your hair of its natural oils, leading to more frizz. Silicones can build up, weighing your hair down and making it look dull.\n* **Heat protection:** If you use heat styling tools, always apply a heat protectant spray beforehand.\n\n**2. Oily Scalp and Heavy Dandruff:**\n\n* **Anti-dandruff shampoo:**  Use a medicated shampoo containing zinc pyrithione, selenium sulfide, ketoconazole, or salicylic acid.  These ingredients effectively target dandruff-causing fungus.  Use it as directed on the bottle, often 2-3 times a week initially, then less frequently as the dandruff improves.\n* **Gentle cleansing:** Avoid over-washing your hair, as this can stimulate oil production. Aim for washing every 2-3 days as you indicated you currently do.\n* **Scalp massage:** Gently massaging your scalp while shampooing can help stimulate circulation and remove excess oil and dead skin cells.\n* **Diet and hydration:**  A healthy diet and adequate water intake can improve overall scalp health. Consider foods rich in omega-3 fatty acids and zinc.\n\n**3. Hormonal Imbalances and Sleep Disturbances:**\n\n* **Consult a doctor:**  The heavy dandruff and other hormonal issues you mentioned warrant a consultation with a doctor or dermatologist. They can determine the underlying cause of your hormonal imbalances and recommend appropriate treatment, which might include blood tests.  Addressing these underlying issues is crucial for long-term hair health improvement.  Your disturbed sleep could also be a contributing factor.\n* **Stress management:**  Stress can exacerbate hormonal imbalances and worsen dandruff.  Practice stress-reducing techniques like yoga, meditation, or deep breathing exercises.\n\n**4'),
(14, 'test@gmail.com', 'Straight Hair', 'Normal', 'Frizzy hair', 'Oily', 'Dandruff', '2-3 days', 'Yes,Heavy dandruff', 'None', 'Other Hormonal Issues', 'Disturbed sleep,I wake up atleast once a night', 'High', 'Never', 'both', 'No', 'Very low in the afternoon', 'None', 'Your oily scalp and dandruff likely stem from hormonal imbalances and stress (sleep disruption).  Use a clarifying shampoo and anti-dandruff treatment regularly. Consider a lightweight conditioner to avoid weighing hair down.  Manage stress for better scalp health.\n'),
(15, 'test@gmail.com', 'Straight Hair', 'Normal', 'Frizzy hair', 'Oily', 'Dandruff', '2-3 days', 'Yes,Heavy dandruff', 'None', 'Other Hormonal Issues', 'Disturbed sleep,I wake up atleast once a night', 'High', 'Never', 'both', 'No', 'Very low in the afternoon', 'None', 'Your oily, straight hair with dandruff needs a clarifying shampoo and a gentle conditioner.  Try a dandruff treatment.  Address hormonal issues with a doctor; better sleep may help reduce stress and dandruff.\n'),
(16, 'test@gmail.com', 'Straight Hair', 'Thin', 'Frizzy hair', 'Oily', 'Dandruff', '2-3 days', 'Yes,Heavy dandruff', 'None', 'Other Hormonal Issues', 'Disturbed sleep,I wake up atleast once a night', 'High', 'Never', 'both', 'No', 'Very low in the afternoon', 'None', 'Your oily, frizzy, thin hair needs gentle cleansing.  Use a clarifying shampoo for dandruff, followed by a lightweight conditioner.  Avoid heavy products. Consider a scalp treatment for dandruff and address hormonal issues with a doctor.\n'),
(17, 'test@gmail.com', 'Straight Hair', 'Thin', 'Frizzy hair', 'Oily', 'Redness', '2-3 days', 'Yes,Heavy dandruff', 'None', 'Other Hormonal Issues', 'Disturbed sleep,I wake up atleast once a night', 'High', 'Never', 'both', 'No', 'Very low in the afternoon', 'None', 'Your oily, frizzy, thin hair needs gentle cleansing.  Use a clarifying shampoo weekly to combat dandruff.  Consider a lightweight, moisturizing conditioner and avoid heavy styling products.  Address hormonal issues with a doctor; improved sleep may help.\n'),
(18, 'test@gmail.com', 'Straight Hair', 'Thin', 'Frizzy hair', 'Oily', 'Redness', '2-3 days', 'Yes,Heavy dandruff', 'None', 'Other Hormonal Issues', 'Disturbed sleep,I wake up atleast once a night', 'High', 'Never', 'both', 'No', 'Very low in the afternoon', 'None', 'Your straight, thin hair needs gentle care.  Use a volumizing shampoo and conditioner to avoid weighing it down.  Target dandruff with an anti-dandruff shampoo.  Since your scalp is oily, wash every 1-2 days instead of 2-3.  Address hormonal issues with a doctor.\n'),
(19, 'test@gmail.com', 'Straight Hair', 'Thin', 'Frizzy hair', 'Oily', 'Redness', '2-3 days', 'Yes,Heavy dandruff', 'None', 'Other Hormonal Issues', 'Disturbed sleep,I wake up atleast once a night', 'High', 'Never', 'both', 'No', 'Very low in the afternoon', 'None', 'Your oily, frizzy, thin hair needs gentle cleansing.  Use a clarifying shampoo for dandruff, followed by a lightweight conditioner. Avoid heavy products.  Address hormonal issues with a doctor; improved sleep may help reduce frizz.\n'),
