conditions (thyroid, disturbed sleep, low energy) are likely impacting your hair health.  It\'s crucial to address these issues with your doctor:\n\n* **Psoriasis Treatment:**  Your dermatologist can recommend appropriate treatments for your psoriasis, such as topical creams or other therapies.  Managing your psoriasis will significantly improve your scalp health and potentially reduce hair loss.\n\n* **Thyroid Management:**  An underactive or overactive thyroid can affect hair growth.  Ensure your thyroid levels are properly managed through medication or other treatments as advised by your doctor.\n\n* **Sleep Hygiene:**  Aim for 7-8 hours of quality sleep per night.  Improving your sleep hygiene can positively impact your overall health, including hair growth.  Consider establishing a relaxing bedtime routine.\n\n* **Dietary Considerations:**');
